Event card
The event card currently uses the generic label “Test Event.” For real events, ensure each card contains a compelling title, a concise description and clear logistics. Here’s a suggested structure:
Event title: Use a descriptive name that highlights the theme (e.g., AI & Data Summit 2026).


Summary line: Summarise the unique value of the event in a short sentence (e.g., “Dive into emerging AI trends and network with global experts.”).


Registration status: Show how many seats are filled (e.g., 25 registered / 100 slots).


Date & time: Present in a clear format (e.g., 4 Feb 2026 · 1:00 PM).


Location: List the venue or virtual platform.


Pricing: Clearly display the starting price or indicate if it’s free.


Call to action: Use a button label such as Register now instead of a small arrow icon.


